# Setting Up Your Product Feed

This guide covers two things:
1. Defining your internal product catalog in `mcp-server/main.py`
2. Understanding what each external platform actually needs so you can write a mapper that converts your catalog into their format

---

## Step 1: Understand your own product data

Before mapping to any external format, write down what you actually have. Every mapper starts from the same internal shape. The template uses a simple Python dict; yours might come from a database, a CSV, or an existing API.

**Audit your data against these questions:**

| Question | Why it matters |
|---|---|
| Do you have a unique, stable ID per SKU? | All three platforms use it to match updates |
| Is your price stored as dollars (float) or cents (int)? | ACP API uses cents; everything else uses dollar strings |
| Do you have variants (size/color)? | Each platform groups variants differently |
| Do you have a product page URL and image URL? | Required by all three platforms |
| Do you have a `brand` field? | Required by Google and ACP |
| What condition? (new / refurbished / used) | Required by Meta; optional for others |
| Do you track availability? | All three require `in_stock` or `out_of_stock` |

**Internal catalog shape in `mcp-server/main.py`:**

```python
PRODUCTS = [
    {
        "id": "sku-001",               # stable, unique — use your real SKU
        "name": "Classic Tee",
        "description": "100% cotton unisex tee. Machine wash cold.",
        "price": 29.99,                # float dollars
        "stock": 50,                   # internal only — never expose to customer
        "brand": "Your Brand",
        "condition": "new",
        "category": "Apparel & Accessories > Clothing",
        "tags": ["tee", "basics"],
        "bestseller": True,
        "image_url": "https://example.com/images/sku-001.jpg",
        "url": "https://example.com/products/sku-001",
    },
]
```

**Required internal fields** — agent uses these:

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | string | Used as the product ID in checkout — must be stable |
| `name` | string | Display name |
| `price` | float | USD dollars |
| `stock` | int | Internal inventory — never expose in agent responses |
| `description` | string | Used in search results |

**Strongly recommended** for external feed mapping:

| Field | Why |
|---|---|
| `brand` | Required by Google and ACP |
| `condition` | Required by Meta |
| `category` | Google product taxonomy path improves ranking |
| `image_url` | Required by all three platforms |
| `url` | Required by all three platforms |

