## Step 3: Write a mapper for each platform you want to support

Once your internal data is clean, the mapper is just a function that transforms one dict shape into another. Build one mapper per platform.

### ACP — ChatGPT / OpenAI

Spec: [developers.openai.com/commerce/specs/file-upload/products](https://developers.openai.com/commerce/specs/file-upload/products)  
Submit: [chatgpt.com/merchants](https://chatgpt.com/merchants) (approved partners)

**Required fields** (file upload format):

| Your field | ACP field | Format |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `item_id` | alphanumeric string |
| `name` | `title` | string, max 150 chars |
| `description` | `description` | string |
| `url` | `url` | full URL |
| `image_url` | `image_url` | full URL |
| `brand` | `brand` | string |
| `price` | `price` | `"29.99 USD"` (dollar string + ISO 4217 code) |
| `stock > 0` | `availability` | `in_stock` / `out_of_stock` / `preorder` |
| — | `is_eligible_search` | `true` to appear in ChatGPT search |
| — | `is_eligible_checkout` | `true` to enable direct purchase |
| — | `seller_name` | your store name |
| — | `seller_url` | your store URL |
| — | `return_policy` | URL to your returns page |
| — | `target_countries` | e.g. `["US"]` |
| — | `store_country` | e.g. `"US"` |

> **Price format**: file upload uses `"29.99 USD"` (human-readable string).  
> The ACP API (PATCH endpoint) uses minor units: `{"amount": 2999, "currency": "USD"}`.  
> These are two different integration paths — don't mix the formats.

**Mapper example:**

```python
def to_acp(product: dict) -> dict:
    availability = "in_stock" if product["stock"] > 0 else "out_of_stock"
    return {
        "item_id":             product["id"],
        "title":               product["name"],
        "description":         product["description"],
        "url":                 product["url"],
        "image_url":           product["image_url"],
        "brand":               product["brand"],
        "price":               f"{product['price']:.2f} USD",
        "availability":        availability,
        "seller_name":         "Your Store",
        "seller_url":          "https://example.com",
        "return_policy":       "https://example.com/returns",
        "target_countries":    ["US"],
        "store_country":       "US",
        "is_eligible_search":  True,
        "is_eligible_checkout": True,
    }
```

**Variants**: use `group_id` (shared across variants) + `variant_dict` (e.g. `{"color": "Blue", "size": "M"}`). Each variant is its own row with a unique `item_id`.

