### Google Merchant Center — Google Shopping + UCP / Gemini

Spec: [support.google.com/merchants/answer/7052112](https://support.google.com/merchants/answer/7052112)  
UCP checkout: [developers.google.com/merchant/ucp/guides/checkout/native](https://developers.google.com/merchant/ucp/guides/checkout/native)  
Submit: Google Merchant Center → Products → Feeds

**Required fields** (applies to all products):

| Your field | GMC field | Format |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `id` | string, max 50 chars |
| `name` | `title` | string, max 150 chars |
| `description` | `description` | string, max 5000 chars |
| `url` | `link` | full URL |
| `image_url` | `image_link` | full URL |
| `price` | `price` | `"29.99 USD"` (number + space + ISO 4217) |
| `stock > 0` | `availability` | `in_stock` / `out_of_stock` / `preorder` / `backorder` |
| `brand` | `brand` | string, max 70 chars (required for most categories) |
| `condition` | `condition` | `new` / `refurbished` / `used` |

> **Price format**: `"29.99 USD"` — number, space, 3-letter ISO 4217 code. Use `.` not `,` as decimal.  
> Do **not** include tax in the price for US/Canada.

**For UCP native checkout**, the product feed submission is just step one. You also need to:
1. Publish a UCP profile at `/.well-known/ucp` on your agent (the template already does this)
2. Implement the checkout REST API: `POST /checkout-sessions`, `PUT /checkout-sessions/{id}`, `POST /checkout-sessions/{id}/complete`
3. Connect your Merchant Center account to UCP via account settings

**Mapper example:**

```python
def to_google_merchant(product: dict) -> dict:
    availability = "in_stock" if product["stock"] > 0 else "out_of_stock"
    return {
        "id":           product["id"],
        "title":        product["name"],
        "description":  product["description"],
        "link":         product["url"],
        "image_link":   product["image_url"],
        "price":        f"{product['price']:.2f} USD",
        "availability": availability,
        "brand":        product["brand"],
        "condition":    product.get("condition", "new"),
        "google_product_category": product.get("category", ""),
    }
```

**Variants**: use `item_group_id` (shared) + individual `size`, `color`, `material` fields per variant.

---

### Meta — Facebook / Instagram Shops

Spec: [facebook.com/business/help/120325381656392](https://www.facebook.com/business/help/120325381656392)  
Submit: Meta Commerce Manager → Catalogs → Data feeds

**Required fields** (physical products):

| Your field | Meta field | Format |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `id` | string, max 100 chars |
| `name` | `title` | string, max 200 chars (recommended < 65) |
| `description` | `description` | plain text, max 9999 chars |
| `stock > 0` | `availability` | `in stock` / `out of stock` (note: two words, no underscore) |
| `condition` | `condition` | `new` / `refurbished` / `used` |
| `price` | `price` | `"9.99 USD"` (number + space + ISO 4217) |
| `url` | `link` | full URL |
| `image_url` | `image_link` | JPEG or PNG, ≥ 500×500px, < 8 MB |
| `brand` | `brand` | string, max 100 chars |

> **Availability values**: Meta uses `"in stock"` and `"out of stock"` (two words, no underscore).  
> Google and ACP use `"in_stock"` (underscore). Don't reuse the same string across mappers.

> **Price format**: `"9.99 USD"` — same pattern as Google. No currency symbols ($, €, £).

**Mapper example:**

```python
def to_meta(product: dict) -> dict:
    # Meta uses "in stock" (two words), not "in_stock"
    availability = "in stock" if product["stock"] > 0 else "out of stock"
    return {
        "id":           product["id"],
        "title":        product["name"],
        "description":  product["description"],
        "availability": availability,
        "condition":    product.get("condition", "new"),
        "price":        f"{product['price']:.2f} USD",
        "link":         product["url"],
        "image_link":   product["image_url"],
        "brand":        product["brand"],
    }
```

**Variants**: use `item_group_id` (shared across variants) + `size`, `color`, `material`, `gender`, `age_group` per variant.  
File formats: CSV, TSV, XLSX, XML — file size limit 100 MB (or 4 GB for scheduled feeds).

